   <text>
      <body>
         <div1 type="calendarCollection">
            <!--div1 just wraps the whole collection. -->
            
            <div2 xml:id="e-1909-05-12"
               facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-12.jpg">
               <!--div2 is for each calendar entry. 
                 1. We can construct an xml:id (to hold a distinct identifier) for this entry:
              it is just the letter "e" followed by the yyyy-mm-dd for the entry, with each piece separated by a hyphen.
                 2. the @facs attribute points to the web URL where we're hosting the calendar images.
              -->
               <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                  NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
               <ab rend="print" hand="#calendarPub">
                  <lb/><date when="1909-03-12">May 12, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday</date>
               </ab>
               <figure rend="color" hand="#multicolor">
                  <figDesc resp="#zmurphy">Drawing of a women in white pushing a stroller, talking to a women in black named Gamie that has a black dog to the left of her.</figDesc>
               </figure>
               <ab hand="#blackpen">
                  <lb/>"There's something queer inside that thing"<lb/> Gamie seems to think- <lb/>"I really dont know what it is <lb/>That can only sleep and drink" </ab>
               <ab><add hand="#redPen" place="bottom-center"><lb/>What do you think is inside!</add></ab>
            </div2>
            
            <div2 xml:id="e-1909-07-13"
               facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/july/1909-07-13.jpg">
               <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                  NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
               <ab rend="print" hand="#calendarPub">
                  <lb/><date when="1909-07-13">May 14, 1909. <lb/>Friday</date>
               </ab>
               <figure rend="cutout">
                  <figDesc resp="#rgerzevske #ebeshero"
                     ><!--ebb: As I zoom in on the image, it's clear this is printed, probably cut out from a magazine. -->
                     A clock that shows the time 5:30 pm.</figDesc>
               </figure>
               <ab hand="#pencil" rend="smallcaps">
                  
                  <lb/>A fiendish invention <lb/> is what I call this<lb/>Without it our lives
                  <lb/><emph style="underline"> would be heavenly bliss! </emph></ab>
                  
                  <ab hand="#redPen"><lb/>ike ask the old thing of!</ab>
                  
               
                    <note resp="#zmurphy">Its clear that Mary really loves her clocks and wouldnt know what to do without a clock. </note>
            </div2>
            
         </div1>
      </body>
